parameters.text:
=Call Get Chapters to retrieve all chapters for the specified book_id: {{ $json.book_id }}

You have access to the following user preferences object:
{{ JSON.stringify($json.preferences) }}

Book Title is: {{ $json.title }}
Author is: {{ $json.author }}


Summarize each chapter as a list of concise bullet points.

Use the "length" parameter to control the level of detail:
- "1pg": Very short — 2–4 bullets per chapter, focusing only on the core message.
- "5pg": Moderate — 6–10 bullets per chapter, capturing key ideas and examples.
- "15pg": Extensive — 12–20 bullets per chapter, covering subtopics, supporting evidence, and nuanced insights.

At the end, include a bullet-point list of overarching takeaways, scaled to the same level of detail.

Return JSON in this format:
{
  "user_preferences": {"style": "bullet_points", "length": "5pg"},
  "chapters_summary": [
    {"chapter_index": 1, "title": "Chapter Title", "summary_bullets": ["• point 1", "• point 2", "• point 3"]}
  ],
  "complete_book_summary": ["• main insight 1", "• main insight 2", "• main insight 3"]
}

=Call Get Chapters to retrieve all chapters for the specified book_id: {{ $json.book_id }}

You have access to the following user preferences object:
{{ JSON.stringify($json.preferences) }}

Book Title is: {{ $json.title }}
Author is: {{ $json.author }}


Summarize each chapter as a clear, workbook-style study section. For each chapter:
- Write a summary scaled to the "length" preference.
- Generate comprehension questions and concise answers, as follows:
  - "1pg": 1–2 simple comprehension questions.
  - "5pg": 3–5 moderate-depth questions covering key ideas and examples.
  - "15pg": 6–8 in-depth questions exploring reasoning, implications, and context.

After summarizing all chapters, include:
- A "complete_book_summary" — a brief synthesis of the book as a whole, scaled to the same level of detail.
- An "index" array mapping every question and answer pair across all chapters.

Return JSON strictly in this format:
{
  "user_preferences": {"style": "workbook", "length": "5pg"},
  "chapters_summary": [
    {
      "chapter_index": 1,
      "title": "Chapter Title",
      "summary": "Short descriptive paragraph(s)",
      "questions": ["Question 1", "Question 2"],
      "answers": ["Answer 1", "Answer 2"]
    }
  ],
  "complete_book_summary": "Concise book overview",
  "index": [{"question": "Question 1", "answer": "Answer 1"}]
}

